---
id: org.dxos.plugin.markdown
name: MarkdownPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Collaborative markdown editor plugin for `DXOS` Composer. Beyond editing, it hosts the document
**review model**: checkpoints, branches and merge (`@dxos/versioning`), the version toolbar/banner
UI, and the ambient Google-Docs-style review surface (Editing / Suggesting / Viewing) that overlays
every author's suggestions and comments on the live editor.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |

## External types & capabilities

The review model composes primitives owned elsewhere:

- `Version`, `Branch`, `History`, `BranchBinding` (`@dxos/versioning`) — named checkpoints, per-object
  branches (`kind: 'draft' | 'suggestion'`), CRDT merge, and the writable per-surface branch binding.
- `SpaceCapabilities.VersioningState` / `ReviewMode` / `ReviewRenderPolicy` / `HistoryProvider`
  (`@dxos/plugin-space`) — the per-user selection + review-mode state, the mode→visibility policy, and
  the generic history-companion gate. This plugin contributes a `HistoryProvider` and consumes the rest.
- `trackChanges`, `suggestions({ base })`, `suggestionsOverlay`, `rebaseHunks`, `diffView`,
  `mergeConflicts` (`@dxos/ui-editor`) — the inline tracked-change / diff / overlay extensions.
- `MarkdownCapabilities.SuggestionSourcesProvider` — the slot plugin-comments contributes to; this
  plugin consumes it to overlay other authors' suggestions without a dependency cycle.
- `CollaborationOperation.AcceptChange` / `RejectChange` (`@dxos/app-toolkit`) — the durable
  cherry-pick/revert ops the ambient accept/reject controls route through.

## Types

```mdl
type ViewMode
  literals: source | preview | readonly
```

```mdl
type DiffView
  literals: inline | sideBySide | gutter | suggest
  desc: How a selected branch is compared against its parent (default `suggest`).
```

```mdl
type Document
  fields:
    name?: string
    fallbackName?: string
    description?: string
    content: Ref<Text>          # collaborative text payload
    history?: History           # checkpoints + branches (@dxos/versioning)
```

```mdl
type Settings
  fields:
    defaultViewMode: ViewMode
    toolbar?: boolean
    numberedHeadings?: boolean
    folding?: boolean
    editorInputMode?: string    # default | vim | vscode
    commentAgentMode?: off | auto | mention
    diffView?: DiffView         # branch compare variant (default suggest)
    experimental?: boolean
    debug?: boolean
```

## Services

```mdl
service HistoryProvider
  desc: |
    Contributes SpaceCapabilities.HistoryProvider for Markdown.Document, so plugin-space renders the
    generic version-history companion (timeline of checkpoints/branches/merges) for markdown docs.
    Resolves the versioned root Text from a document.
  methods:
    getTarget(object: Obj.Unknown) -> Text?
```

```mdl
service SuggestionSourcesConsumer
  desc: |
    MarkdownArticle consumes MarkdownCapabilities.SuggestionSourcesProvider (contributed by
    plugin-comments) to enumerate every active suggestion branch and overlay them, diffed against
    main, on the ambient editor. plugin-markdown never imports plugin-comments (capability only).
```

## Components

```mdl
component MarkdownArticle
  desc: |
    Full-surface markdown editor for a Document or Text subject. Beyond editing it drives the review
    model: an advanced path (explicit branch/checkpoint/fork selection via the version toolbar) and
    the ambient default path (selection === current) that overlays all authors' suggestions + comments
    per the per-user review mode. Suggesting mode binds the editor to the user's own suggestion branch
    (edits accrue there, never to main) and renders them as character-level tracked changes.
  props:
    subject: Document | Text
    viewMode: ViewMode
    settings: Settings
  state:
    selection?: range           # current editor selection
    mode: ReviewMode            # editing | suggesting | viewing (per-user, per-doc)
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode         # formatting toolbar + version toolbar
  actions:
    setViewMode(mode: ViewMode)
    setMode(mode: ReviewMode)
    uploadFile(file: File) → Ref<Image>
  emits:
    onSelectObject(id: string)  # follow @ref or link

component VersionToolbar
  desc: |
    The version-review banner row shown above the editor while off "main @ now": a slim strip for the
    active checkpoint / branch / fork (at most one selected). Owns restore / branch-from / merge /
    view-select / close handlers. (Renamed from VersionBanners.)
  props:
    versioning: UseVersioningResult

component VersionBanner
  desc: |
    A single banner (checkpoint | branch | fork). Branch mode carries the Base/Diff/Branch view
    selector; suggestion branches show the author's name + hue.
  props:
    mode: checkpoint | branch | fork
    name: string
    view?: BranchView
  emits:
    restore, branchFrom, viewChange, close

component MarkdownCard
  desc: Read-only preview card for embedding a Document in other surfaces.
  props:
    subject: Document | Text

component EditableMarkdownCard
  desc: Inline-editable card variant used when data.editable is true.
  props:
    subject: Document | Text
```

## Operations

```mdl
op create
  desc: Creates a new markdown Document and adds it to the active space.
  input: { name: string, content: string }
  output: string                # DXN of created Document
  effects: [echo:write]

op open
  desc: Reads the current contents of a markdown Document.
  input: { doc: Ref<Document> }
  output: string
  effects: [echo:read]

op update
  desc: Applies a set of find/replace edits to a markdown Document (optionally on a branch).
  input: { doc: Ref<Document>, edits: Edit[], branchId?: string }
  output: string
  errors: { NotFound: oldString not present in document }
  effects: [echo:write]

op CreateBranch
  desc: Fork a core branch off main (or a checkpoint), returning the branch's canonical content DXN.
  input: { doc: Ref<Document>, name?: string, from?: { target, heads } }
  effects: [echo:write]

op MergeBranch
  desc: CRDT-merge a branch back into main and archive its registry entry.
  input: { doc: Ref<Document>, branchId: string }
  effects: [echo:write]

op CreateCheckpoint
  desc: Record a named checkpoint (Version) of main or the selected branch's heads.
  input: { doc: Ref<Document>, name?: string, target?: Ref<Text> }
  effects: [echo:write]

op SuggestEdit
  desc: |
    Find-or-create the caller's per-author `kind:'suggestion'` branch and apply edits to it, so the
    proposal accrues for review rather than mutating main. Creator defaults from the ambient agent
    identity when absent.
  input: { doc: Ref<Document>, edits: Edit[], creator?: string }
  effects: [echo:write]

op scrollToAnchor
  desc: Scrolls the editor for the attendable surface to a cursor position.
  input: { subject: string, cursor: string, ref?: string }
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Edit Document

  req F-1.1: Editor opens Document.content as a collaborative CodeMirror surface.
  req F-1.2: Edits replicate to all peers via ECHO Text.
  req F-1.3: Document.name renders as the surface title; fallbackName used when name is empty.

feat F-2: View Modes

  req F-2.1: Document opens in settings.defaultViewMode (source | preview | readonly).
  req F-2.2:
    when: user toggles view mode
    then: editor switches between source and preview; state persists per Document
  req F-2.3:
    when: viewMode is readonly
    then: editor is non-editable; toolbar hidden

feat F-3: Formatting Toolbar

  req F-3.1:
    when: settings.toolbar is true
    then: formatting toolbar shown above editor with bold, italic, headings, lists, links
  req F-3.2: Toolbar surfaces toolbar-disposition actions from the app graph for the current attendable.

feat F-4: Inline References

  req F-4.1:
    when: user types `@` in the editor
    then: link query opens with objects from the active space
  req F-4.2:
    when: user selects a reference
    then: a link to the object DXN is inserted at the cursor
  req F-4.3:
    when: user clicks a reference
    then: LayoutOperation.Open invoked for the linked object

feat F-5: File Upload

  req F-5.1:
    when: user drops an image onto the editor
    then: file uploaded via AppCapabilities.FileUploader and inserted as a markdown image

feat F-6: AI Editing

  req F-6.1: Plugin contributes a Skill exposing op:create, op:open, op:update as tools.
  req F-6.2:
    when: agent invokes op:update
    then: edits applied as ordered oldString → newString diffs against Document.content

feat F-7: Comments

  req F-7.1: Editor supports anchored comment threads on text ranges (via plugin-comments'
    ExtensionProvider).
  req F-7.2:
    when: settings.commentAgentMode is `auto`
    then: every new user message in a thread triggers the comment agent
  req F-7.3:
    when: settings.commentAgentMode is `mention`
    then: agent responds only when the message contains its @name

feat F-8: Versioning (checkpoints, branches, merge)

  req F-8.1: The plugin MUST support named checkpoints (CreateCheckpoint), per-object branches
    (CreateBranch), and CRDT merge-back (MergeBranch) over Document.history (@dxos/versioning).
  req F-8.2: The plugin MUST contribute a HistoryProvider for Markdown.Document so plugin-space
    renders the generic history companion (checkpoint/branch/merge timeline).
  req F-8.3: The VersionToolbar MUST let the user select main / a branch / a checkpoint / a fork,
    with a Base/Diff/Branch view selector for a selected branch (default Diff on toolbar switch).
  req F-8.4: Selecting a branch/checkpoint/fork MUST NOT mutate main; edits on a branch accrue to
    that branch's Text via a per-surface BranchBinding.

feat F-9: Ambient review (Editing / Viewing)

  req F-9.1: In the default view (selection === current) the editor MUST overlay every active
    suggestion branch (via the SuggestionSourcesProvider capability), diffed against main, plus
    comments — gated by ReviewRenderPolicy(mode).
  req F-9.2: Editing overlays suggestions + comments and is editable; Viewing hides suggestions,
    keeps comments, and is read-only. The mapping is a product-configurable policy.
  req F-9.3: The advanced (explicit-selection) path MUST be unaffected by the ambient overlay.
  req F-9.4: Accept/reject of a suggestion MUST route through the durable CollaborationOperation
    AcceptChange / RejectChange (diffed against main), never a direct splice.

feat F-10: Suggesting mode (authoring)

  req F-10.1:
    when: mode === 'suggesting' (ambient path)
    then: the editor binds to the current user's own `kind:'suggestion'` branch (find-or-create) so
      typed edits accrue there and render as character-level tracked changes vs main; edits MUST
      never touch main (the mount is guarded until the branch binding resolves).
  req F-10.2: Other authors' suggestions MUST overlay against main (base-decoupled), excluding the
    current user's own branch (shown as tracked changes, not doubled).
  req F-10.3: A multi-line/block deletion MUST render its removed text with line breaks preserved;
    undo MUST re-instate a deleted region (no bespoke un-delete affordance).

feat F-11: Independence

  req F-11.1: plugin-markdown MUST NOT import plugin-comments source; the comment + suggestion-source
    wiring is via MarkdownCapabilities slots only.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create document
  given: user has an open space
  when: op:create invoked with { name: "Notes", content: "# Hello" }
  then:
    - new Document persisted to ECHO
    - Document.name === "Notes"
    - Document.content target contains "# Hello"

test T-2: Apply edit
  given: Document.content is "There is a tyop."
  when: op:update invoked with edits [{ oldString: "tyop", newString: "typo" }]
  then:
    - Document.content becomes "There is a typo."

test T-3: Toggle view mode
  given: Document open, settings.defaultViewMode === source
  when: user toggles view mode
  then:
    - editor renders preview
    - reload restores preview mode for this Document

test T-4: Reference autocomplete
  given: Document open, space contains object "ProjectX"
  when: user types `@Proj`
  then:
    - link query shows ProjectX
    - selecting it inserts a DXN link at the cursor

test T-5: Branch, edit, merge
  given: A document on main
  when: A branch is created, edited, and merged back
  then:
    - the branch edit lands on main after merge; a `merge:` checkpoint is recorded
    - the branch edit never appeared on main before merge

test T-6: Ambient overlay + mode
  given: A document with two seeded suggestion branches, selection === current
  when: mode is Editing
  then:
    - both authors' suggestions overlay the editor and comments are shown
  when: mode switches to Viewing
  then:
    - suggestions are hidden, comments remain, the editor is read-only

test T-7: Suggesting mode authors on the user's branch
  given: A document, selection === current, mode === suggesting
  when: the user types
  then:
    - the edit renders as a self tracked-change
    - main/root content is unchanged; the user's suggestion branch gained the edit
    - a second author's suggestion still renders vs main and does not strike the user's new text
```

